        "title": "function argument as case expression",
        "body": "<p>The following function is supposed to calculate the i-th smallest element of a sorted list that it takes as argument.\nI wanted to use a \"<em>switch<\/em>\" expression inside my function instead of \"<em>if<\/em>\".<\/p>\n\n<p>The compiler gives me the following error : \"<em>case expression must be constant expression<\/em>\"<\/p>\n\n<p>Please note that the function is obviously not complete.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public int search(int[] a, int i) {\n    ArrayList &lt;Integer&gt; smaller_than = new ArrayList &lt;Integer&gt; ();\n    ArrayList &lt;Integer&gt; greater_than = new ArrayList &lt;Integer&gt; ();\n    int pivot = a[i];\n\n    for (int j = 0; j &lt; a.length; j++) {\n        if (a[j] &lt; pivot) {\n            smaller_than.add(a[j]);\n        }\n\n        if (a[j] &gt;= pivot) {\n            greater_than.add(a[j]);\n        }\n    }\n\n    switch (smaller_than.size()) {    \n        case i:\n            return greater_than.get(1); &lt;----    \n    }\n\n    return 0;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I would like to know how can I satisfy the case expression requirement, knowing that a parameter taken as argument has to be declared as constant.<\/p>\n",
